## Repository layout

```
<project>/
├── apps/
│   ├── backend/         # <one-line>
│   └── frontend/        # <one-line>
├── docker/              # compose files per deployment mode
├── infra/               # config baked into containers (nginx, postgres init)
├── data/                # bind-mount targets, gitignored except .gitkeep
├── docs/                # documentation-template site
├── scripts/             # subscripts called by ./dev
├── dev                  # one-command boot
├── .env                 # secrets, gitignored
├── .env.example         # the contract, committed
└── README.md / CLAUDE.md
```

## Hard rules

(Replace with the 3–7 rules that override defaults for this project.)

- **Every component uses `var(--token)` from `tokens.css`** — no hex, no raw px in component CSS.
- **Per-service `config.yaml`** reads root `.env` via `${VAR}` interpolation; never put secrets in `config.yaml`.
- **Frontend env is scoped** — `apps/frontend/.env` holds `VITE_*` only; backend secrets stay in root `.env`.
- **No `src/` at repo root** — always nested under `apps/<name>/src/`.
- **`./dev` is the only entrypoint** — setup folds in. No separate `setup.dev.sh`.
- **File size cap: 500 hard / 300 soft.** Split before committing.
- **Folders by feature, not by kind.** `auth/`, `workspaces/`, `blocks/` each own routes + models + service.

